  "text": "Atoh1-Cre transgenic (TG) mice [CITATION_1] and Rac1 flox/flox mice [CITATION_2] Cells, chemicals, plasmids and RNA interference RN46A [CITATION_3] , PC12 [CITATION_4] and HEK293 (ATCC) cells were used in the present study (for details on cell maintenance, see the supplementary Materials and Methods). EHop-016, which inhibits Rac GEF interaction and has 100-fold higher specificity than the established Rac inhibitor NSC23766 [CITATION_5] , was obtained from Millipore. The details of plasmids and RNA interference are described in the supplementary Materials and Methods.",
